The paper deals with the problem of discovering the semantic structure of visual data, which is a core problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also addresses the issue of incomplete and sparse tags, which is a common problem in information retrieval (cs.IR). The proposed method involves machine learning techniques, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with multi-media data, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing techniques to deal with textual tags, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
